Should be fairly straightforward to install (Famous last words).
However, Your mileage may vary (YMMV) due to the presence or lack of
libraries already installed in your system.

You may wish to acquire

PNG: libpng-1.2.29.tar.bz2
     http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html
     http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/libpng/libpng-1.2.29.tar.bz2?download
     ftp://ftp.simplesystems.org/pub/libpng/png/src/libpng-1.2.29.tar.bz2
     http://download.sourceforge.net/libpng/libpng-1.2.29.tar.bz2

JPEG: jpeg-6b/
      http://www.ijg.org/
      ftp://ftp.simtel.net/pub/simtelnet/msdos/graphics/jpegsr6.zip
      http://www.ijg.org/files/
      ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/

ZLIB: zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz
      http://www.zlib.net/
      
and you must have IMLIB

// http://freshmeat.net/projects/imlib/
// http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/imlib/
// http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/imlib/
// http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/imlib/1.9/imlib-1.9.15.tar.bz2
// http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/imlib/1.9/imlib-1.9.15.tar.gz


Start here...  If you have difficulties, let us know and we will
modify where possible...

make
make install
